text: November unemployment rates ranged from 1.8% in MD to 5.4% in NV.
Only Hawaii and DC saw house prices fall between Q3 2022 and Q3 2023.
State real GDP in Q3 2023 was higher than in Q3 2022 in all states except Delaware.
Nov average private weekly earnings in states ranged from $880 in MS to $1,367 in WA.
Manufacturing jobs in Nov 2023 were at or above Nov 2019 levels for 29 states.
Q3 2023 retail real GDP growth over the year was at least 8% in every state and DC.
Unemployment rates in Nov 2023 were lower than in Nov 2019 in 25 states.
MN and 31 other states have seen continuous growth in house prices since Q1 2013.
Public jobs in Nov 2023 were at or above Nov 2022 levels in all but two states.
